[start section id="20112"]

This case was discussed and supervised by Dr. Calderon, and Si Ester, P.A.-C., was also present.
#1 Adenocarcinoma of the rectum involving the posterior vaginal wall
She has completed neoadjuvant radiation therapy with 5-FU as a radiosensitizer with her last dose on June 17, 2010.  Ms. Jean Murphy now needs to be evaluated for surgery, and this is in process with a CT of the chest, abdomen, and pelvis being scheduled along with a consultation by Radiation Oncology to consider any role of intraoperative radiotherapy. The gynecologists are also being consulted for their help in the setting for surgical intervention on her vaginal wall involvement.
#2 Preoperative assessment
Ms. Jean Murphy is having a chest x-ray and ECG along with lab work prior to surgery.  Her performance status is currently 1, and if her labs and imaging and ECG come back within normal limits, she is clear for surgery.
#3 Nicotine dependence
We are referring Ms. Jean Murphy to our Nicotine Dependency Service to aid in this since this will be crucial to aid in healing postoperatively.
ADVANCE DIRECTIVES
Advance directive or living will: No, not interested in additional information.
PATIENT EDUCATION
Ready to learn, no apparent learning barriers were identified; learning preferences include listening.  Explained diagnosis and treatment plan; patient expressed understanding of the content.

