[start section id="20103"]

Ms. Murphy Murphy is a very pleasant 38-year-old Wvklpd-Hscudkou lady from Austin, who comes to the Clinic today accompanied by her mother.  She has had a three-year history of constipation, and initially this was thought to be secondary to analgesic medication which she was taking for back pain.  Use of laxatives did not improve her symptoms, and two years ago, she developed rectal bleeding which she describes as dark red blood mixed with the stool.  In April 2010, she had the colonoscopy which essentially showed a mass in the rectum which was biopsy-proven as adenocarcinoma.  She had a PET CT-scan performed on April 9, 2010, which showed disease within the rectum and pelvis with an 8-mm left iliac node.  She was given a staging of T4 N1 M0.  On April 13, 2010, due to the near-obstructing lesion in her rectum, a sigmoid loop diverting colostomy was performed in addition to an EUS and also an examination under anesthesia that was performed which demonstrated a nodular lesion in the rectum penetrating the anal canal and also nodularities in the posterior vaginal wall.  A left subclavian Port-a-Cath was also inserted.  She was commenced on neoadjuvant therapy with radiation and 5-FU as a radiosensitizer in May 2010 and completed 6 cycles.  Treatment was held on June 3 due to skin toxicity, but she states that her last radiation was on June 17.  Surgery was then planned, but there were some issues with her financial status, and so she has subsequently come to GCGH for further evaluation.
Over the last months, she has remained reasonably asymptomatic with no issues with her colostomy or considerable issues with pain.
Her comorbidities include having a previous cholecystectomy (exact reason unknown).  She had previous spine surgery for lumbar disk protrusion at the level of L3, L4.  She has a history of depression with alcohol dependence, but she states that she has not had an alcoholic drink for the last five to six-months.  She is a current smoker, having started smoking at the age of 13 and currently has a 25-year smoking history at one-pack-a-day.
She has three children at-home, a 5-year-old son, a 2-year-old son, and a 21-year-old daughter.  She is currently not working.

[end section id="20103"]

